doctype html
html
	head
		- const pageSegment = "clutch"
		- const projectTitle = "Célio Pires - Clutch"
		- const projectDescription = "The \"System of Systems\"—a visual builder powered by atomic design principles."
		//- CANONICAL
		- const pageCanonical = `https://celiopires.com/${pageSegment}`
		//- GLOBAL META TAGS
		- const pageTitle = projectTitle
		- const description = projectDescription
		- const image = "defaultImage"
		//- FACEBOOK META TAGS
		- const facebookTitle = projectTitle
		- const facebookDescription = projectDescription
		- const facebookImage = "defaultFacebookImage"
		//- TWITTER META TAGS
		- const twitterTitle = projectTitle
		- const twitterDescription = projectDescription
		- const twitterImage = "defaultTwitterImage"
		include includes/head
	body
		include includes/nav
		#Clutch.clutch
		.container
			// Intro Header
			#intro__header.container__intro
				.intro__header--bottom
					.role__industry
						ol
							li
								div.font__small-3 Role
								div.font__small-3 Senior Product Designer
							li
								div.font__small-3 Year
								div.font__small-3 2020 - 2021
							li
								div.font__small-3 Industry
								div.font__small-3 SaaS, NoCode, LowCode
					h1.font__extra-large-1 Clutch
					p.font__medium-3
						| The "System of Systems"—a visual builder powered by atomic design principles.
					.picture__center--full-screen
						img(src='assets/images/clutch/clutch03.jpg' alt='Clutch is a webapp this is the main desktop interface')
						.caption
							.font__small-3 Clutch is a webapp this is the main desktop interface
			.container__box
				.paragraph__box--1col
					.box__header-small
						h2.font__small-2 Project Overview
					.box__body
						p.font__small-1
							| Clutch is a next-generation visual builder that allows teams to build enterprise-grade React applications visually. Unlike traditional "No-Code" tools, Clutch reads and writes real code (React, Next.js, Tailwind), serving as a unified workspace where design intent translates directly into production infrastructure.
				.paragraph__box--1col
					.box__header-small
						h2.font__small-2 My Role: Design System Architect
					.box__body
						p.font__small-1
							| As a Senior Product Designer, I was responsible for the architecture of the platform's internal Design System and some parts of the interface. My goal was to design a UI that could interpret and manipulate complex CSS logic without breaking the code structure.
				.paragraph__box--1col
					.box__header-small
						h2.font__small-2 The Challenge
					.box__body
						p.font__small-1
							| To create a "property taxonomy" that bridges the gap between Designer (Tokens/Visuals) and Developer (Utility Classes/Code).
				.paragraph__box--1col
					.box__header-small
						h2.font__small-2 Key Contributions
					.box__body
						p.font__small-1
							| Built the dense, high-performance component library used to construct the Clutch IDE itself, ensuring it could handle complex data states.
				.picture__center--full-screen
					img(src='assets/images/clutch/clutch01.jpg' alt='Clutch - Layer panel in detail')
					.caption
						.font__small-3 Clutch - Layer panel in detail
				.picture__center--full-screen
					img(src='assets/images/clutch/clutch02.jpg' alt='Clutch - Properties panel')
					.caption
						.font__small-3 Clutch - Properties panel
		include includes/footer
